== Failure Rate Calculation

Using formula: $"failure rate" = 1 - "accuracy"^"steps"$

#table(
  columns: (1fr, 1fr, 1fr, 1fr),
  stroke: 0.5pt + rgb("#ccc"),
  inset: 8pt,
  fill: (_, row) => if row == 0 { rgb("#f0f0f0") } else if row == 2 { rgb("#e8f5e9") } else { none },
  [*Per-step accuracy*], [*3 steps (min)*], [*5 steps (current)*], [*10 steps (bloated)*],
  [95%], [14.3%], [22.6%], [40.1%],
  [*98%*], [*5.9%*], [*9.6%*], [*18.3%*],
  [99%], [3.0%], [4.9%], [9.6%],
)

#block(fill: rgb("#e3f2fd"), inset: 12pt, radius: 4pt, width: 100%)[
  *Recommendation:* Keep 5-step design. With strict schema + middleware validation, per-step accuracy reaches ~98%, yielding *9.6% failure rate*. Focus on raising per-step accuracy (cheaper) rather than reducing steps (loses functionality).
]

== Environment Honesty

#block(fill: rgb("#f3e5f5"), inset: 12pt, radius: 4pt, width: 100%)[
  *Assessment:* Two strong enforcement layers (Architecture + Middleware) that the model cannot bypass, plus one weak layer (Prompt). *Adequate for a recommendation agent.* \
  \
  *WARNING -- NOT adequate for:* Financial transactions, medical advice, or any high-stakes operations without additional human-in-the-loop gates.
]

